Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Boil your #kettle{}, then pour the @water{500}(for the stock) into a #measuring jug{}. Add the @chicken stock paste{20} and stir well to combine - this is your chicken stock.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{3}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #ovenproof pan{} on medium heat.

> TIP: If you don't have an ovenproof pan, use a normal saucepan and transfer to an ovenproof dish later.

Once hot, add half the garlic and stir-fry for ~{30%seconds}, then add the @risotto rice{175}. Stir and cook until the edges of the rice are translucent, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in the chicken stock and bring back up to the boil, then pop a #lid{} on the pan (or cover with #foil{}) and bake on the middle shelf of your oven until the rice is cooked and the water has been absorbed, ~{20-25%minutes}.

While the risotto bakes, sandwich each @British chicken breasts{2} between two pieces of #baking paper{} or #cling film{}.

Pop onto a #board{}, then give it a bash with the bottom of a #saucepan{} or #rolling pin{} until it's 1-2cm thick.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Pop the chicken into a #bowl{} with the @dried rosemary{1}, remaining garlic and a drizzle of @oil{}. Season with @salt and @black pepper, then mix well.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the oil is hot, lay in the chicken. Fry until golden brown, ~{5-6%minutes} each side.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Once cooked, transfer the chicken to a board, cover with foil and rest for a couple of minutes.

When the risotto is cooked, remove it from the oven and mix in the @peas{120}, @butter{20} and @grated hard Italian style cheese{40}.

Season to taste with @?salt and @?black pepper if needed.

> TIP: Add a splash of water to loosen the risotto if needed.

When everything's ready, cut the chicken into 6 slices widthways.

Share the risotto between your #bowls{} and top with the rosemary chicken.

Finish with a drizzle of @fresh pesto{32}.

Enjoy!